# Memory Persistence

- Before exploring a workflow, read the relevant files in this order: workflow seed, prior learnings, discovery maps, and shared memory notes — all under the app's directory (`apps/<app-name>/`).
- Do not rely on chat history as durable memory. Persistent knowledge must be stored in the repository.
- After each meaningful exploration or test run, update the workflow learnings and any affected shared memory files under the relevant app directory.
- Reuse existing selectors, success signals, and prior findings before rediscovering the same UI.
- Mark statements as confirmed only when directly observed. Keep assumptions and open questions separate.
- If a learned behavior becomes outdated, replace it with the latest observed behavior and note the change.
